-- Colombian Stock Movers: Avianca Taca Holding, Canacol Energy
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-03-08T21:35:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/colombian-stock-movers-avianca-taca-holding-canacol-energy.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. Bogota time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 1 percent to 14,973.10, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.7 percent to 1,724.74.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA)  (PFAVTA CB), the owner of
 Colombia ’s largest airline, rose 2.3 percent, the most in a
week, to 4,140 pesos.  The company said 2011 profit increased 221 percent from a
year ago to 202 billion pesos ($114 million), according to an e-
mailed statement today.  The company’s board of directors proposed a dividend
payment of 50 pesos per share to be paid after April 27 in one
allocation, according to a regulatory filing late yesterday.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in Colombia, gained 2.6 percent to
1,760 pesos.  The company said it found oil in its Ranch Hermoso 15 and
17 wells, according to a regulatory filing today. The drilling
results are “encouraging,” according to an e-mailed report
from Celfin Capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
